EBS = Elastic Block Store
-------------------------

-Its a block storage service used with EC2 instances.
-Think of it a virtual hard disk(with HDD/SSD attached to your running EC2 instance)-virtual server
-EBS specially desgined for EC2 instance
-If EC2 is the computer, then EBS is the disk storage


Why EBS is used?
-----------------
Used when you need:
-OS installation disk for EC2
-Persistent storage after reboot
-Database storage
-Application files
-Logs storage
-Backup via Snapshots

Key Feature:
------------
Persistent storage: If EC2 stops/restarts, data remains
Attach/Detach: You can attach and detach volumes multiple times or you can detach volume from one EC2 and attach to another EC2 (SAME AZ)
Resize Anytime: Increase size without deleting disk

Snapshot Backup:
Take backup to S3 (managed internally by AWS)

EBS is high performance with SSD/HDD options availale

Types of EBS Volumes:
---------------------
A. SSD Types: gp3 (recommended) General purpose SSD

used for : Web servers, medium databases, Dev/test

B. HDD Type
st1 Throughput optimized HDD
used for: Big data, Logs, Streaming 


Example Real-Time DevOps Usage:
--------------------------------
Example1: EC2 Linux Server
-Launch EC2
-Root volume=30GB gp3 EBS
-Install application

Example2: Database Server
-EC2+MYSQL
-Separate EBS volume 500GB io2

Note:
1.When you you attaching NEW EBS volume to running EC2 instance the EBS volume should same Availability zone
